						<div class="postbody">I'd say make it for the PC using Pygame, trying to respect the NES limits as best you can. A Pygame game can be played on any platform that supports Python and SDL 1.2, which includes Windows, OS X, GNU/Linux, and Android. I've done this a bit myself: <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=109649#p109649" class="postlink">Wrecking Ball Boy</a>, <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=112810#p112810" class="postlink">FHBG remake</a></div>

